- cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper presents a method to speed up essential routines in power systems, such as stochastic planning, operations, and controls. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a numerical method to solve the resulting nonlinear optimization problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a sparse generalized polynomial-chaos expansion to provide useful statistical information. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with power systems and their probabilistic behavior. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper suggests a model to exploit the underlying low-rank and sparse structure of high-dimensional simulation data arrays.
